ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Mnemonic Similarity Task First or second stimulus in pair
Mnemonic Similarity Task Number of stimuli from other pair
Stimulus type (Similar to stimulus shown during learning phase, same and new stimulus not shown)
How similar a new stimulus is to an old stimulus shown during the learning phase?
Notes: 1= Not similar at all; 5= Very similar

ElementDescription: Elapsed time (milliseconds) from the begging of the task

Notes: name of image displayed; -7 = N/A as image was not displayed in this trial

ElementDescription: Key pressed: On learn phase trials
